    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stamps that share the appearance of conventional postage stamps, including size, perforated edges, and in some cases imagery, but that are created and used by artists engaging in the practice of mail art.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000076053/Welch, Eternal Network: Mail Art Anthology (1995)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049770/Welch, Networking Currents (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Postzegels die eruitzien als gewone postzegels, door de grootte en de gekartelde rand en soms de afbeelding die erop staat, maar die zijn gemaakt door kunstenaars en door hen worden gebruikt in het kader van mail art.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>具有傳統郵票的尺寸和打孔邊緣外觀的印花，有時包含圖像，而該圖像係由實踐郵件藝術的藝術家所設計出與使用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
